time required: 45 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @Red Onion{1}(halved and cut into ½-inch-thick wedges) into ½-inch-thick wedges. Strip @Rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4). Halve, core, and cut @Apple{1}(halved, cored, and cut into ½-inch-thick wedges) into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes, carrots, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon}, chopped rosemary, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. (Divide between 2 #baking sheets{} for 4 servings; roast on top and middle racks.)

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the pork and apple then).

While veggies roast, pat @Pork Tenderloin{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with remaining Fry Seasoning, salt, and pepper. Rub with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}.

Once veggies have roasted 10 minutes, add pork to same baking sheet. Carefully toss apple with veggies. (For 4 servings, add pork to one sheet and apple to other.)

Return to top rack until veggies are browned and tender and pork is cooked through, ~{18-22%minutes} more. (For 4, return sheet with pork and veggies to top rack and sheet with apple and veggies to middle rack.)

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @Honey{2%teaspoon}, and @Dijon Mustard{4%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Once pork is done, carefully transfer to a #cutting board{}. Let rest at least ~{5%minutes}, then thinly slice crosswise.

> TIP: Love extra-crispy veggies? While pork rests, heat broiler to high and return veggies to oven, 2-3 minutes more.

Divide roasted veggies and apple and pork between plates. Serve with creamy mustard on the side for dipping.